b'The first Parisian retrospective dedicated to Gabrielle Chanel in Paris, the \xe2\x80\x98Gabrielle Chanel. Fashion Manifesto\xe2\x80\x99 exhibition highlights the development of her style, the characteristics of her work, the emergence of her codes, and her contribution to the history of fashion. 

The exhibition is running until March 14th at the Palais Galliera in Paris with the support of CHANEL. 

#ExpoCHANEL #CHANEL @Palais_Galliera #PalaisGalliera'

b'A look into the \xe2\x80\x98Gabrielle Chanel. Fashion Manifesto\xe2\x80\x99 exhibition at the Palais Galliera in Paris. A retrospective recounting the early beginnings of the \xe2\x80\x98couturi\xc3\xa8re\xe2\x80\x99 with a few emblematic\xc2\xa0creations which defied the prevailing fashions of her time. \xc2\xa0

The exhibition is running until March 14th at the Palais Galliera in Paris with the support of CHANEL.\xc2\xa0 \xc2\xa0

#ExpoCHANEL #CHANEL @Palais_Galliera #PalaisGalliera'

b'\xe2\x80\x98Gabrielle Chanel. Fashion Manifesto\xe2\x80\x99 exhibition \xe2\x80\x94 The first Parisian retrospective dedicated to Gabrielle Chanel is running from October 1st to March 14th at the Palais Galliera, the City of Paris Fashion Museum, with the support of CHANEL.

Gabrielle Chanel devoted her life to creating a new kind of elegance based on freedom of movement and a natural attitude free from extravagance. This was her \xe2\x80\x9cfashion manifesto\xe2\x80\x9d, a heritage that is more relevant than ever in today\xe2\x80\x99s world.

#ExpoCHANEL #CHANEL @Palais_Galliera #PalaisGalliera'

b'Gabrielle Chanel\xe2\x80\x99s engagement in the world of dance endures as the House supports and collaborates with ballet companies around the world. Experience the story that continues to move in the new episode of Inside CHANEL on IGTV.\n\n#InsideCHANEL #GabrielleChanel'

b'CHANEL upholds the legacy of Gabrielle Chanel by supporting and collaborating with L\xe2\x80\x99Ope\xcc\x81ra de Paris, English National Ballet and, starting in 2021, The Australian Ballet. Experience the enduring story of Gabrielle Chanel and dance in the latest episode of Inside CHANEL, available now on IGTV.\n\n#InsideCHANEL #GabrielleChanel @operadeparis @englishnationalballet @ausballet'

b'Gabrielle Chanel shared a lifelong friendship with dancer and choreographer Serge Lifar, who considered her his artistic godmother. Step into the story of Gabrielle Chanel and the pioneers of modern dance, watch the latest episode of Inside CHANEL on IGTV.\n\n#InsideCHANEL #GabrielleChanel'

b'Gabrielle Chanel brought her vision of the liberated woman to dance, designing costumes that allowed for the ultimate freedom of movement. Discover the story in the new chapter of Inside CHANEL on IGTV.\n\n#InsideCHANEL #GabrielleChanel'

b'Gabrielle Chanel freed women from their corsets and went on to design costumes that celebrated the bodies of modern dancers. Her free spirit made the perfect partner for this art form, the ultimate expression of movement. Experience the story that continues to move on the in the newest episode of Inside CHANEL on IGTV.\n\n#InsideCHANEL #GabrielleChanel'

b'Gabrielle Chanel studied with the great dancers Caryathis and Isadora Duncan. She brought the art form\xe2\x80\x99s freedom of movement to fashion, and then went full circle as a costume designer for the Ballets Russes. See the story in the new episode of Inside CHANEL, Gabrielle Chanel and dance on IGTV.\n\n#InsideCHANEL #GabrielleChanel'

b'Gabrielle Chanel and dance held a natural affinity, the art form being the ultimate expression of movement. Discover how she brought the fashion world into modern dance on IGTV.\n\n#InsideCHANEL #GabrielleChanel'

b'For Gabrielle Chanel, dance was a revelation, an art form that influenced her approach to design, and was interlaced throughout her life. Introducing the latest episode of Inside CHANEL, Gabrielle Chanel and dance, available on IGTV.\n\n#InsideCHANEL #GabrielleChanel'

b'Gabrielle Chanel left her mark on the world of modern dance at a pivotal time for the art form, creating costumes that allowed performers to move freely, and supporting troupes and choreographers as a friend, creative partner and patron. Her friendship with Serge Diaghilev, the flamboyant, visionary producer of the Ballets Russes, lasted until the end.
The House of CHANEL upholds this legacy today through its support of ballet companies worldwide. In the latest episode of Inside CHANEL, see the entrancing, enduring story of Gabrielle Chanel and dance.

#InsideCHANEL\xc2\xa0#GabrielleChanel'
